From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: James Shkolnik <jshkolnik@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 12 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] orangepi4pro: disable unused UFS controller

The board has no UFS device (uses microSD / eMMC / NVMe). The enabled UFS
controller spends ~5s at boot failing link startup (UFS_EVT_LINK_STARTUP_FAIL)
and logging errors. Disable it.

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun60i-a733-orangepi-4-pro.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun60i-a733-orangepi-4-pro.dts
index 4468cc2e6..cbe74fbf7 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun60i-a733-orangepi-4-pro.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun60i-a733-orangepi-4-pro.dts
@@ -3826,6 +3826,6 @@ &ufs {
        vcc-supply = <&reg_dldo6>;
        vccq-supply = <&reg_dcdc8>;
        vccq2-supply = <&reg_dcdc8>;
-       status = "okay";
+       status = "disabled";
 };

